Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  VI. ... it shall be lawful for Her Majesty ... to constitute ... a General Assembly in and for

the Islands of New Zealand, to be called the General Assembly of New Zealand, which said General Assembly shall consist of and be holden by the Governor ..., and a Legislative Council, and a House of Representatives; ...
Notes:  1846 Aug 28 An Act to make further provision for the government of the New Zealand Islands (9 and 10 Vict. c. 103) in 1949 Rutherford ed. Select Documents 20



