Quote:  The localisation of the land fund ... was the inevitable result of the

Ultra-Provincialism which [Grey] did his best to introduce. Unconstitutionally he started the provinces before the General Assembly - thus launching the constitution [441] `bottom upwards' as old Charleton used to say.
Notes:  C.W. Richmond

