Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  Collins Concise English Dictionary
Author:
Vol / Page:  463
Edition:
Quote:  General Assembly  ... 2. N.Z. an older name for parliament. Now in occas. elliptical use for General Assembly Library, the library (now part of the National Library) attached to Parliament and housed as an adjunct to parliament Buildings. also G.A.
Notes:  nf. 1986 NZPOD; 1985 Collins NZ Compact Dict. 206

